156
0:09:42.16,000 --> 0:09:52,000
Video: This Earth is four and a half billion years old.

157
0:09:55.16,000 --> 0:09:59,000
These plants, several hundred million years old.

158
0:10:00.16,000 --> 0:10:03,000
And we humans have been walking upright

159
0:10:03.16,000 --> 0:10:06,000
for only 200 thousand years.

160
0:10:08.16,000 --> 0:10:09,000
We've managed to adapt,

161
0:10:09.16,000 --> 0:10:12,000
and have conquered the whole planet.

162
0:10:15.16,000 --> 0:10:18,000
For generations, we've been raising our children,

163
0:10:18.16,000 --> 0:10:21,000
not unlike millions of other species living beside us.

164
0:10:24.16,000 --> 0:10:26,000
For the past 30 years

165
0:10:26.16,000 --> 0:10:29,000
I've been closely watching the earth and its dwellers

166
0:10:29.16,000 --> 0:10:31,000
from high up in the sky.

167
0:10:31.16,000 --> 0:10:36,000
Our life is tied to the well-being of our planet.

168
0:10:36.16,000 --> 0:10:39,000
We depend on water,

169
0:10:39.16,000 --> 0:10:41,000
forests,

170
0:10:41.16,000 --> 0:10:44,000
deserts,

171
0:10:44.16,000 --> 0:10:47,000
oceans.

172
0:10:47.16,000 --> 0:10:49,000
Fishing,

173
0:10:49.16,000 --> 0:10:51,000
breeding,

174
0:10:51.16,000 --> 0:10:53,000
farming

175
0:10:53.16,000 --> 0:10:56,000
are still the world's foremost human occupations.

176
0:10:58.16,000 --> 0:11:,000
And what binds us together

177
0:11:00.16,000 --> 0:11:04,000
is far greater than what divides us.

178
0:11:04.16,000 --> 0:11:09,000
We all share the same need for the earth's gifts --

179
0:11:09.16,000 --> 0:11:11,000
the same wish to rise above ourselves,

180
0:11:11.16,000 --> 0:11:13,000
and become better.

181
0:11:16.16,000 --> 0:11:18,000
And yet we carry on raising walls

182
0:11:18.16,000 --> 0:11:21,000
to keep us apart.

183
0:11:21.16,000 --> 0:11:23,000
Today our greatest battle

184
0:11:23.16,000 --> 0:11:26,000
is to protect the natural offerings of our planet.

185
0:11:26.16,000 --> 0:11:28,000
In less than 50 years

186
0:11:28.16,000 --> 0:11:3,000
we've altered it more thoroughly

187
0:11:30.16,000 --> 0:11:33,000
than in the entire history of mankind.

188
0:11:33.16,000 --> 0:11:36,000
Half of the world's forests have vanished.

189
0:11:36.16,000 --> 0:11:38,000
Water resources are running low.

190
0:11:38.16,000 --> 0:11:41,000
Intensive farming is depleting soils.

191
0:11:43.16,000 --> 0:11:46,000
Our energy sources are not sustainable.

192
0:11:46.16,000 --> 0:11:48,000
The climate is changing.

193
0:11:48.16,000 --> 0:11:51,000
We are endangering ourselves.

194
0:11:51.16,000 --> 0:11:54,000
We're only trying to improve our lives.

195
0:11:54.16,000 --> 0:11:57,000
But the wealth gaps are growing wider.

196
0:11:57.16,000 --> 0:11:59,000
We haven't yet understood

197
0:11:59.16,000 --> 0:12:02,000
that we're going at a much faster pace

198
0:12:02.16,000 --> 0:12:04,000
than the planet can sustain.

199
0:12:24.16,000 --> 0:12:28,000
We know that solutions are available today.

200
0:12:30.16,000 --> 0:12:33,000
We all have the power to change this trend

201
0:12:33.16,000 --> 0:12:35,000
for the better.

202
0:12:40.16,000 --> 0:12:42,000
So what are we waiting for?

